result.execSummary:
The defendant Jaccqlyn R Ratzlaff was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jaccqlyn R Ratzlaff is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jaccqlyn R Ratzlaff was found guilty of Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jaccqlyn R Ratzlaff in court with attorney Daniel Francis Snyder.  Matthew J Tingstad appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA calls case at 10:53 a.m.  Cites appearances.  Atty Snyder states agreement.  DA agrees with Atty Snyder's recitation.  Court Dismisses Count #1.  PLQ submitted.  Def pleads NC per Atty Snyder.  Court questions def.  No coercion to plead NC.  Court questions def re PLQ.  Def admits signing.  No coercion.  Atty Snyder satisfied def freely, knowingly and intelligently pleads.  Court accepts plea and finds def guilty of Count #2.  Sentence withheld, 1 year probation, joint restitution of $2270.50.  20 days ICA with credit for 20 days, no further jail obligation.  Costs of $243, DNA on file so no sample or surcharge.
